# Data Display Grouping Convention

All record/entity data must be displayed in **grouped sections** with related information together. Never render flat key-value dumps.

## Shared components

| Component | Location | Purpose |
|-----------|----------|---------|
| `AccountingRecordView` | `components/policies/tabs/AccountingTab.tsx` | Renders premium records with sections, entities, formatted values |
| `AccountingSection` | same file | Renders one cover-type section (e.g. "Third Party", "Own Vehicle Damage") |
| `PolicySnapshotView` | `components/policies/PolicySnapshotView.tsx` | Renders package snapshots grouped by package with labels |

## Rules

1. **Same data, same component** — if the same data type appears in multiple pages (e.g. premium data on both Policy details and Premium Record details), use a single shared component. Never duplicate rendering logic.

2. **Group by logical entity** — premium fields go under their cover-type section (Third Party / Own Vehicle Damage). Entity info (Collaborator, Insurer, Agent) displays at section or record level, not mixed into field rows.

3. **Formatted values** — currency fields use `fmtCurrency()`, percentages append `%`, booleans show "Yes"/"No", selects resolve to option labels. Never show raw stored values.

4. **Inline rendering for "self" context** — when a record page displays its own data (e.g. Premium Record showing its own premium info), render the shared component inline on the Overview, NOT in a separate tab. Use `context="self"` with `AccountingTab`.

5. **Entity resolution fallback** — for `context="self"`, if entities (Collaborator, Insurer, Agent) are not found in the record's own snapshot, fall back to the linked policy's snapshot via `resolveEntitiesFromSnapshot()` in `app/api/policies/[id]/premiums/route.ts`.

6. **Hidden raw packages** — when a shared component renders a package's data (e.g. `AccountingTab` renders premium data), hide the raw package from `PolicySnapshotView` via the `hiddenPackages` prop to avoid duplication.

## Example: Premium Record on Overview

```tsx
{/* Hide raw premium package from generic snapshot view */}
<PolicySnapshotView
  detail={detail}
  hiddenPackages={new Set(["accounting", "premiumRecord"])}
  canEditPremium={isAdmin}
  onPremiumUpdate={refresh}
/>
{/* PolicySnapshotView internally renders AccountingTab with context="self" */}
```
